Download this sucker and then try the following:  get a hold of virtualdub (a great open source video editing program) as well as the deflicker, fx deghost, and unsharp mask filters, then re-export this thing adding the filters in this order:
1. unsharp mask
2. de-ghost
3. resize to 484x260
4. crop to 480x256
5. deflicker
6. unsharp mask again (less strong)
7. up the saturation and brightness a bit

You have to play around with the settings, but you will end up with a video that is noticeably better quality. If only the cammer had done all that.  Oh yeah, also add a highpass filter to the audio (cutoff at 25 Hz) to remove some of the low base/echoes. Virtualdub does this.
